Exploration was the ultimate frontier, and it promised

00:01:23.937 --> 00:01:29.197
fortune, glory, and the chance to write your name into history.

00:01:30.097 --> 00:01:37.207
Into this era stepped Percy Harrison Fawcett: a dashing, determined British explorer

00:01:37.487 --> 00:01:43.877
with an uncanny ability to survive conditions that killed lesser men in days.

00:01:44.996 --> 00:01:52.646
In 1925, at the age of 58, he ventured deep into the Amazon rainforest

00:01:52.886 --> 00:01:59.486
on a quest for what he believed was a lost city—a place he called “Z.”

00:02:00.366 --> 00:02:06.126
But shortly after the journey began, he vanished without a trace,

00:02:06.466 --> 00:02:10.856
leaving behind a mystery that would captivate the world for decades.

